org.gradoop.flink.io.impl.edgelist

Class VertexLabeledEdgeListDataSource

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.gradoop.flink.io.impl.edgelist.EdgeListDataSource
      • org.gradoop.flink.io.impl.edgelist.VertexLabeledEdgeListDataSource
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    DataSource

    public class VertexLabeledEdgeListDataSource
extends EdgeListDataSource
    Data source to create a LogicalGraph from an edge list. Vertices are annotated with a string label/value, e.g. 0 EN 1 ZH 2 DE 0 EN The example line denotes an edge between two vertices: First edge: source: with id = 0 and vertex value "EN" and target: with id = 1 and vertex value "ZH". Second edge: source: with id = 2 and vertex value "DE" and target: with id = 0 and vertex value "EN". This data source implementation will create a logical graph based on the specified edge list. The resulting vertices will have a user-defined property that stores the label/value. The type of that value will be string.
